Word2Vec is a word embedding technique that learns meaningful vector representations of words.

It uses two training strategies:

CBOW (Continuous Bag of Words): Predicts the target word from the surrounding context words.
Skip-Gram: Predicts the surrounding context words from a given target word.

CBOW is faster and performs well for common words, while Skip-Gram is slower but learns better representations for rare words.

