Word2Vec

Word2Vec is a technique that converts words into meaningful vectors (embeddings).

It has two strategies:

CBOW (Continuous Bag of Words)
Skip-Gram
1. Continuous Bag of Words (CBOW)
Idea

Given the surrounding (context) words, predict the missing (target) word.

Example

Sentence:

I love to eat pizza

Suppose the target word is eat.

Input (context words):

I   love   to   ____   pizza

Output:

eat
Another Example

Sentence:

She is reading a book

Input:

She   is   ____   a   book

Output:

reading
Real-world Analogy

Your friend says:

"I drink ___ every morning."

You can easily guess:

coffee



