2. Skip-Gram
Idea

Given one target word, predict the surrounding (context) words.

Example

Sentence:

I love to eat pizza

Target word:

eat

Output:

love
to
pizza
Another Example

Sentence:

She is reading a book

Target:

reading

Output:

is
a
book
Real-world Analogy

Someone says only:

coffee

You immediately think of related words like:

drink
morning
tea
cup

One word helps predict its surrounding words.

